  <!-- Start Main Content -->

<br>
<div class="heading_c"> Welcome to <i><b><font color="#be1e2d">RED</font></b><font color="black">fly</font></i> </div>
<div class="heading_release_c">
<p>
<i><b><font color="#be1e2d">RED</font></b><font color="black">fly</font></i> version 3 released!<br>
See <a target="_blank" href="http://nar.oxfordjournals.org/content/early/2010/10/20/nar.gkq999">the recent NAR paper</a> for a description of our new features and new interface.
</p>
<p>
<span style="font-size:14pt;"><a href="mailinglist.php">Sign up</a> to receive
announcements about important <b><i><b><font color="red">RED</font></b><font color="black">fly</font></i></b> news.</span>
</p>
</div>



<div class="watermark">
<p>
<i><b><font color="#be1e2d">RED</font></b><font color="black">fly</font></i> is a curated collection of known <i>Drosophila</i> transcriptional
cis-regulatory modules (CRMs) and transcription factor binding sites
(TFBSs). Despite more than 20 years of experimental determination of
these elements, the data have never been collected into a single
searchable database. REDfly seeks to include all experimentally
verified fly regulatory elements along with their DNA sequence, their
associated genes, and the expression patterns they direct. Expression
patterns are annotated using a <a href="
http://obo.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/detail.cgi?fly_anatomy">defined
anatomy ontology</a> to enable high interoperability with <a href="
http://flybase.bio.indiana.edu/">FlyBase</a>, <a href="
http://www.flyexpress.net/">FlyExpress</a>, the <a href="
http://insitu.fruitfly.org/cgi-bin/ex/insitu.pl">BDGP in situ
hybridization database</a>, and other model organism resources.  </p>

<p>
If you know of experimentally verified cis-regulatory elements that
are not included in the REDfly database, or have corrections to the
archived data, please <a href="contact.php">contact us</a>.

</p>
<p>
<i><b><font color="#be1e2d">RED</font></b><font color="black">fly</font></i> has 898 CRMs associated with 325 genes, and
1427 TFBSs bound by 96 transcription factors acting on 110 target genes.
These data are based on 447 curated publications. 
</p>
<p align='center'>
<span style="font-size:14pt;"><a href="search.php">Search <i><b><font color="red">RED</font></b><font color="black">fly</font></i></a></span>
</p>

</div>
